All CT images of patients were converted to the grey-scale, and then reviewed by a radiologist with more than 15 years of experience in thoracic imaging. Fig. 1
indicates the CT sample images of patients with COVID-19 and other atypical and viral pneumonia diseases. The radiologist defined the rectangular region of infections on CT images. Then, the regions were cropped and resized to 60 × 60 pixels (Fig. 2
). One region of infection was defined per slice for further analysis. The largest region was selected if there are more than one regions of infections.
